      "writtenOn": "2022-01-27T08:33:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "does rust have conventions around context manager naming or usage ?  or does it have conventions with methods providing a context manager on the fly such that it could be a method on Minijail ?\n\nor maybe something more heretical: since rust manages life cycles all the time, is there a situation where we would ever actively be leaking a jailed process ?  like, what if this was just how Minijail worked ?",
      "parentUuid": "f5012b30_7eff9a8f",
      "revId": "8f3e04cca1c2a3330e27b0b3efc542f8015a736a",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
